# Capacitor Polarity Classification - Experiment Results

## Dataset

- Total labeled images: 159
- Classes: Top, Bottom, Left, Right
- Train: 127 images
- Validation: 16 images
- Test: 16 images

## Model Comparison

| Model | Validation Accuracy | Test Accuracy |
|---------|---------|---------|
| CNN | 68.75% | 81.25% |
| MobileNetV2 (Frozen) | 87.50% | 68.75% |
| MobileNetV2 (Fine-Tuned) | 68.75% | 75.00% |

## Key Findings

- Custom CNN achieved the best test accuracy (81.25%).
- MobileNetV2 achieved strong validation accuracy but did not generalize as well on the test set.
- Fine-tuning MobileNetV2 improved test accuracy from 68.75% to 75.00%.
- Class imbalance affected performance, particularly for the Right class.
- Analysis of confusion matrices showed that several errors occurred on boundary cases where marker orientation was ambiguous.
- For this dataset size, the simpler CNN generalized better than the larger transfer-learning model.

